# GoArrive — Cline Rules

## Project
GoArrive is an online fitness coaching platform. React Native + Expo + Expo Router + Firebase. Single codebase for web, iOS, Android. Multi-tenant, three roles: platformAdmin, coach, member.

## Stack
React Native, Expo, Expo Router, TypeScript (strict), Cloud Firestore, Firebase Auth, Cloud Functions Gen 2, Firebase Hosting, Stripe Connect, Zoom API, Google Calendar API.
NO MySQL, TiDB, Drizzle, Fastify, or S3.

## Critical Auth Pattern
Always use `effectiveUid` or `claims.coachId` from `useAuth()` — never `user.uid`.
All coach-scoped queries must include `where('coachId', '==', coachId)`.
Admin impersonation breaks if this pattern is violated.

## Code Conventions
- camelCase everywhere: Firestore docs, TS interfaces, props, state
- Product language: "coach" not trainer, "member" not client, "movement" not exercise, "Command Center" not dashboard
- FlatList for lists > 500 items
- thumbnailUrl for initial media loads, never full video on first render
- Soft deletes with isArchived flag, never hard delete

## Three Roles Only
platformAdmin, coach, member. No CoachAssistant, Encourager, or any fourth role.

## Build Tab & Workouts
Workout creation starts on a blank block canvas, NOT a metadata form.
Movements use 4:5 aspect ratio.
Build tab is unified workspace (replaces separate Workouts and Movements tabs).

## Testing
- Vitest for logic: `cd apps/goarrive && npm run test:vitest`
- Playwright for E2E: `npm run test:e2e`

## Deployment
- Always staging first: `cd apps/goarrive && npm run deploy:staging`
- Never production without explicit approval

## Do Not Build
MySQL, TiDB, Drizzle, S3, Fastify, JotForm, Calendly, Zoom Embedded SDK, additional roles, white-label, custom domains.

## Deep Knowledge
See .claude/ directory for 17 detailed knowledge base documents covering every aspect of the platform.
